          <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Are security cameras better than security guards?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Security cameras provide 24/7 coverage, recorded evidence, and wider area monitoring at lower cost. Guards offer human intervention and flexibility. Many sites use both for comprehensive protection.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Can surveillance trailers replace security guards?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Yes, surveillance trailers can replace guards for many applications including construction sites, parking lots, and storage yards. They provide continuous monitoring, recording, and remote response capabilities.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">What about response time when something happens?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Security trailers provide instant alerts to monitoring centers and law enforcement. While guards can intervene directly, trailers often result in faster police response due to verified video evidence of crimes in progress.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">Do security trailers work in bad weather?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Yes, security trailers are designed for all-weather operation. They continue monitoring in rain, snow, and extreme temperatures where human guards might seek shelter or have reduced effectiveness.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA Section -->
    <section class="py-16 bg-blue-900 text-white">
